
[1]demarkation

   DEMARKATION, n.

   1. The act of marking, or of ascertaining and setting a limit.

   2. A limit or bound ascertained and fixed; line of separation marked or
   determined.

   The speculative line of demarkation, where obedience ought to end and
   resistance begin, is faint, obscure, and not easily definable.
